.SH "NAME"
ata_dev_revalidate \- Revalidate ATA device
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.HP \w'int\ ata_dev_revalidate('u
.BI "int ata_dev_revalidate(struct\ ata_device\ *\ " "dev" ", unsigned\ int\ " "new_class" ", unsigned\ int\ " "readid_flags" ");"
.SH "ARGUMENTS"
.PP
\fIdev\fR
.RS 4
device to revalidate
.RE
.PP
\fInew_class\fR
.RS 4
new class code
.RE
.PP
\fIreadid_flags\fR
.RS 4
read ID flags
.RE
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
Re\-read IDENTIFY page, make sure
\fIdev\fR
is still attached to the port and reconfigure it according to the new IDENTIFY page\&.
.PP
LOCKING: Kernel thread context (may sleep)
.SH "RETURN"
.PP
0 on success, negative errno otherwise
